'''Liz Holliday''' is a British editor and writer of science fiction and mystery, who was the author of the ''[[The Official Star Wars Fact File]]'', published [[2002]] through [[2005]].

She also edited the magazines ''Odyssey'' and 3SF, and was fiction editor for ''Valkyrie'' magazine for its first thirteen issues.

She has written novelizations of British television programs, including ''Cracker'' and ''Soldier Soldier''.

Holliday's short stories have appeared in numerous anthologies and magazines, including ''Dragon''. Her story "''And She Laughed''" was adapted for television as an episode of ''The Hunger'' in 1999.

